# Testing & Quality

## Definition of Done (every task)

| Change | Required |
|--------|----------|
| Domain rule | Unit test (Vitest) |
| Use case | Integration test (PG via Testcontainers) |
| New permission endpoint | RBAC test (allow + deny + cross-tenant fail) |
| Payment flow | API E2E test |
| Bug fix (financial) | Regression test **before** fix |

## Golden Rule

> Financial bug → write failing test first → then fix

## TypeScript

- `strict: true`
- No `any` (use `unknown` + narrow)
- Shared types: `packages/contracts` only

## Git / PR

- One concern per PR — no drive-by refactor
- Format: `type(scope): description` — e.g. `feat(installments): add create sale`
- Update `.env.example` for new env vars
- ❌ secrets in git

## Logging

Structured JSON — `{ tenantId, event, entityId }`  
❌ `console.log` in production code paths

## Before Merge Checklist

- [ ] `EXCELLENCE-STANDARDS.md` §9 (DB / backend / UI as applicable)
- [ ] lint + typecheck pass
- [ ] relevant tests pass
- [ ] no `tenant_id` query missing filter
- [ ] contracts updated if API changed
- [ ] docs/ADR if behavior/architecture changed

